	   <tr><td colspan=2>   A few months ago, I decided that I wanted to start a cleric. My options were Gnome, Dwarf, High Elf, Human, Dark Elf, Euridite, and maybe Halfling and Half Elf. I was also well aware how many clerics were High Elfs and Dwarfs. Frankly, High Elfs have better starting stats, and dwarfs tend to be easy to play.<br><br>I chose to play a dark elf. Why?<br><br>1. Dark Elves look hell a cool.<br>2. Evil classes and races need more healers.<br>3. Starting stats are nice.<br>4. You get HIDE which will save your life if you are in a dangerous place and are still LFG.<br>5. VI has put in a few DE items that make being a DE a little easier.<br><br>Hard part. The faction makes you KOS in a lot of norath. Banking sucks, and long trips to find a merchant that will sell to you also sucks. If you have played "good race/classes", you may not be able to play in the same areas you have before.<br><br>I suggest these zones for theses levels.<br><br>(1-6) Nektulos forest; newbie crap<br>(6-10) West commons; at orc camps<br>(10-13) East commons; Kodiaks, and Skells in Befallen<br>(13-18) Oasis; crocks and orcs<br>(19-28) Lake of Ill Omen; sarnaks and everything else<br>(29-39) The Overthere; everything (there is a bank and merchants for DE here)<br>(39-45) The Dreadlands; group at Nwall<br>(46- ) ?<br><br>I hope you chose to play a DE, it may be a little harder at times, but deffinetly worth it. If you are not a DE, the lvl/zone thing should aply to you too. Cleric Power!!<br><br>Becursed into Darkness<br>42nd Sphere of Innoruuk's hate<br>Member of the Scarlet Underground<br>in the land of Terris-Thule<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
