	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, best race for a cleric:  depends on what you're going after.  Personally, I went with high elf because that's where the WIS was, and later down the road what is going to matter most to me?  That little bit of mana for that last heal that can save someone.  However, the best race argument all depends on what exactly you're looking for.  If you want to be unique, go with the DE.  If you want to be able to carry more than just food, components, and cash later, go with a dwarf.  You get the point.<br>Soloing:  Clerics are not meant to solo.  HOWEVER, a low level cleric can whoop some undead butt.  Best place?  Unrest.  Once you get above a certain level (I think LOIO was when it started getting difficult), soloing blues will barely seem possible.  If you chose to play a cleric, then you may want to get used to the life a cleric leads, and get in a group as much as possible.  Druids are known for their solo kiting abilities, so if you want a class that can solo and heal, go with them.<br>Other than that, remember your job, keep your group alive, and uphold the name of clerics.  You may not be the best meleer or nuker, but you will definitely come out being the hero plenty of times.<br><br>Crysandra Healwind<br>Priestess of Tunare<br>Dragon Warriors - E'ci<br>&nbsp;<br>Crysandra Healwind<br>Priestess of Tunare<br>Destiny Awaits - E'ci<br>crysandra_healwind@yahoo.com</td></tr>
