<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98824161686539></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98824161686539><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=7&mid=98824161686539>Soloing</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=774><span id= >Puggins</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>9 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Apr 25th 7:33 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>52nd level cleric here.  I can tell you this: if you can't solo at 13th level, you do not have the proper equipment.  And by proper equipment, I don't mean all the +wis items you can stack on.<br><br>Here's a reality check: at 13th level, every point of wisdom is worth an additional 2.5 points of mana.  So those +2 wisdomr rings are giveing you +5 mana each, and that batfang headband gives you a little less than +8 mana.  Between them, they don't even give you an extra nuke.<br><br>So what do you do?  Simple- get rid of them.  Get a banded helmet for starters, upgrade to a bronze helm if you can stand the weight, and then to a Skull--shped barbute when you can afford it.  Get a pair of jagged bands- they don't cost any more than 50pp each, maxx.  That mace of yours is better than what I had at that level.  Get a decent shield- chitin shell shield is cheap- to go with it.<br><br>Get your AC up and you WILL be able to solo at your level, with no problems.  I was able to solo throughout my career when my normal group wasn't on.  By 18th to 20th level, you won't be able to melee creatures to death, but you'll still be able to kill them by DDing them while meleeing them.  By mid-thirties, it makes NO sense to even try to melee, and you go standard root-nuke.<br><br>But at 13th level, you're barely worse than standard tanks are at meleeing.  You should be able to smash 'em down.<br>&nbsp;<br>Puggins Fizzlefoot<br>Personal Footgroomer for Fizzlethorpe Bristlebane, Bless his hairy little toes<br></td></tr>
