	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Are Clerics better than paladins - YES!!!<br><br>Do Clerics fight better than Paladins - No<br><br>They are 2 completely different classes to play.  The Cleric is the Master Healer, always wanted in a group and will keep a group alive with many different abilities from heals to stuns to the Occasional Nuke (VERY occassional).  The Paladin will wade into combat and deal melee damage after sharing his/her minor buffs with the group and will help heal the party after the fight is over.  Paladins also use stuns and undead dd spells to assist in combat but they do most damage with their weapons.<br><br>If you want to be a fighter be a Paladin, a Clerics life is spent in the spell book medding.  Paladins are Tanks, Clerics are Support Class.  <br><br>Vildaar<br>lvl 19 DE Cleric<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
