	   <tr><td colspan=2>There is a question about skill caps (melee skills) that has always kept me wondering. Three questions, actually, now that I think about it. <br><br>1) If you neglect 2HB (as I have, for example) it seems to take much longer to raise it later on from its lower level. For example, if I am level 10 and my 1HB is kept capped, it doesn't seem to take long to keep it capped. But if my 2HB is only at skill 15 or so, it seems to take forever to get it to 16, and forever to get it to 17, and forever to get it to 18, etc... Am I missing something? This leads to my second question.<br><br>2) Is skill increase tied to only the number of "swings" you are taking or is it also tied to the difficulty of the mob you are facing (i.e. the higher level mob, the quicker your skill increases)? <br><br>3) Is it true that melee skill caps for clerics only increases by 4 for each level while it increases by 5 for everyone else?<br><br>These are but a few of my wonderings. (I wonder as I wander) If anyone knows the answer to these questions I would certainly appreciate an answer posted here for all to see. I can't believe that I am the only one who has wondered about this. <br><br>And if you are so inclined, I would also appreciate the answer via email at greg@arihood.com (since I frequently forget where I have posted questions and where to look for the responses!) <br><br>Thanks much!<br>&nbsp;<br>Botten Baggens<br>6 Earthen Lane<br>Rivervale<br>Saryrn<br><br>Galius Dalmatius<br>N. Freeport<br>Saryrn</td></tr>
