<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98821002378213></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98821002378213><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=7&mid=98821002378213>RE: hell levels?</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=35078><span id= >Gestalt</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>87 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Apr 25th 10:47 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Agi influences ac and being hit/missed.  A characters agi has no bearing on whether or not he'll hit or miss his opponent.  Dex and str will help raise offensive skills (as should wis/int whichever is higher), Agi does the opposite, helps increase def and dodge type skills but won't make a player dodge more (with the skill), but if enough agi, could help mob just plain miss you more often.  However, when Agi is 75+, it doesn't make a big difference, you need a LOT of it to notice a change in mobs hitting you, though it never hurts either!  =)  Beware Agi below 75, as you take a huge ac hit.  AC is definately a clerics best friend next to wis/mana, and sometimes moreso depending on where he/she is atm.<br>&nbsp;<br>Gestalt<br>52 Monk<br>CT</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
