	   <tr><td colspan=2>Nice to see somebody using trade skills for the roleplay aspect. Chakfor is a master baker/brewer/potter/ and drinker. <br><br>I found pottery easy to do and very very cheap. Just go to Thurgardin to do it. You've got a sketch vendor and a clay vendor about 10 feet from the wheel and kiln and the only times I've seen them used is when I was doing it.<br><br>Baking was easy and it's used in some quests. I'm not doing a guide for this one. There's already plenty of those around.<br><br>Brewing isn't for high elves. As a dwarf I like making my own brews and while drinking them in a group you can get some good conversations started. And for those who say you shouldn't be drinking while grouped I say this: Just don't drink enough to get drunk :) You're a wis caster, not an int caster.<br><br>Any trade skill except jewelcraft is nice. Clerics really don't have a skill made just for them but all have their rewards. Tailoring is AWESOME when your skill is high enough. The velious tailored armor is better than some gear looted in 50+ zones. The only problem is getting the ingredients :(<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
